TelephonyInfosProxy * mpTelephonyInfosProxy

Detailed Description

The class to provide base facility to access Telephony related content, which is stored in a SQLite database and in the file system.

The following example demonstrates how to use this TelephonyInfos class.

 addTelephonyInfos() {
     // Add a TelephonyInfos
     Context* context = new Context(this);
     TelephonyInfos* telephonyInfos = new TelephonyInfos(*context);
     ContentValues* cv = new ContentValues();

     cv->addValue(TelephonyInfos::NAME(), name);
     cv->addValue(TelephonyInfos::APN(), apn);
     cv->addValue(TelephonyInfos::PROXY(), proxy);
     cv->addValue(TelephonyInfos::PORT(), port);
     cv->addValue(TelephonyInfos::MMSPROXY(), mmsProxy);
     cv->addValue(TelephonyInfos::MMSPORT(), mmsPort);
     cv->addValue(TelephonyInfos::USER(), user);
     cv->addValue(TelephonyInfos::SERVER(), server);
     cv->addValue(TelephonyInfos::PASSWORD(), password);
     cv->addValue(TelephonyInfos::MMSC(), mmsc);
     cv->addValue(TelephonyInfos::TYPE(), type);
     cv->addValue(TelephonyInfos::AUTH_TYPE(), authVal);
     cv->addValue(TelephonyInfos::MCC(), mcc);
     cv->addValue(TelephonyInfos::MNC(), mnc);

     telephonyInfos->add(TelephonyInfos::URI(), *cv);

     delete context;
     delete telephonyInfos;
     delete cv;
 }

 showEditAndDeleteTelephonyInfos() {
     Context* context = new Context(this);
     TelephonyInfos* telephonyInfos = new TelephonyInfos(*context);
     StringArray selection(5);
     selection.replaceAt(TelephonyInfos::NAME(), 0);
     selection.replaceAt(TelephonyInfos::APN(), 1);
     selection.replaceAt(TelephonyInfos::USER(), 2);
     selection.replaceAt(TelephonyInfos::SERVER(), 3);
     selection.replaceAt(TelephonyInfos::PASSWORD(), 4);

     // Show TelephonyInfoss
     Cursor* cr = telephonyInfos->getN(TelephonyInfos::URI(),
         &selection, NULL, NULL, &TelephonyInfos::ORDER());

     if (cr != NULL && cr->getCount() > 0) {
         cr->moveToFirst();
         do {
             String name = cr->getString(0);
             String apn = cr->getString(1);
             String user = cr->getString(2);
             String server = cr->getString(3);
             String password = cr->getString(4);

             // ...
         } while (cr->moveToNext());
     }
     // Close the cursor
     cr->close();

     // Edit a TelephonyInfos
     ContentValues* cv = new ContentValues();
     cv->addValue(TelephonyInfos::PASSWORD(), newPassword);

     Uri uri1 = ContentUris::withAppendedId(TelephonyInfos::URI(), updateId);
     telephonyInfos->set(uri1, *cv, NULL, NULL);

     // Delete a TelephonyInfos
     Uri uri2 = ContentUris::withAppendedId(TelephonyInfos::URI(), deleteId);
     telephonyInfos->remove(uri2, NULL, NULL);

     delete context;
     delete telephonyInfos;
     delete cv;
 }

See the sample given above. There are four operations about TelephonyInfos: add, edit, show and remove.

Query the given table, returning a Cursor over the result set.

Parameters:
uriThe requested uri.
selectionA list of which columns to return. Passing null will return all columns, which is discouraged to prevent reading data from storage that isn't going to be used.
whereA filter declaring which rows to return, formatted as an SQL WHERE clause (excluding the WHERE itself). Passing null will return all rows for the given table.
whereArgsYou may include ?s in where, which will be replaced by the values from whereArgs, in order that they appear in the where. The values will be bound as StringArray.
sortHow to order the rows, formatted as an SQL ORDER BY clause (excluding the ORDER BY itself). Passing null will use the default sort order, which may be unordered.
Returns:
A Cursor object, which is positioned before the first entry. Note that Cursors are not synchronized, see the documentation for more details.

The caller should delete the returned object to release the allocated memory when the object is not used anymore.

static base::String gaia::content::TelephonyInfos::SPN_STRINGS_UPDATED_ACTION ( ) [static]

Broadcast Action: The Service Provider string(s) have been updated.

Activities or services that use these strings should update their display. The intent will have the following extra values:

  • showPlmn - Boolean that indicates whether the PLMN should be shown.
  • plmn - The operator name of the registered network, as a string.
  • showSpn - Boolean that indicates whether the SPN should be shown.
  • spn - The service provider name, as a string.

Note that showPlmn may indicate that plmn should be displayed, even though the value for plmn is null. This can happen, for example, if the phone has not registered to a network yet. In this case the receiver may substitute an appropriate placeholder string (eg, "No service").

It is recommended to display plmn before / above spn if both are displayed.

Note this is a protected intent that can only be sent by the system.
